## Wire it into an app (manual steps the generator can't do)

1. Add the dependency to the app: `"@acme/{{ kebabCase name }}": "workspace:*"`.
2. Add the API route handler:

   ```ts
   // apps/nextjs/src/app/api/trpc/{{ kebabCase name }}/[trpc]/route.ts
   import { fetchRequestHandler } from '@trpc/server/adapters/fetch';

   import { appRouter, createTRPCContext } from '@acme/{{ kebabCase name }}/server';

   const handler = (req: Request) =>
     fetchRequestHandler({
       endpoint: '/api/trpc/{{ kebabCase name }}',
       req,
       router: appRouter,
       createContext: () => createTRPCContext({ headers: req.headers }),
     });

   export { handler as GET, handler as POST };
   ```
{{#if react}}
3. Wrap the relevant tree with `{{ pascalCase name }}TRPCReactProvider` (from `@acme/{{ kebabCase name }}`).
{{/if}}
4. Register the schema for migrations (drizzle config `schema` glob), then `pnpm db:push`.
{{/if}}